values:
So I guess I bitch to much in my livejournal... ill try and not do that so much.

Me and a few of my friends got into an interesting discussion last night... What exactly is hooking up? Girls seem to think it can be used for just about anything from making out to having sex, but guys are saying they would only say "I hooked up" if they had sex. If you don't say hooked up what terminology do you use? Fooled around to me sounds more crude than "hooked up" but then again its just more specific. I would like some feedback.. girls and guys please... what does "hooking up" mean?

This weekend was amazing for the record. I went to Brad and Schotte's Friday and Saturday night. Friday night after the party I went to Ross street to watch Curb Your Enthusiasm with the guys, and Greenaway fell asleep sitting up.. it was really funny and I wish I had thought to take a picture. The cops busted the party up Saturday night (I think they came Friday night also but I might not have been there anymore...) The cop thing is a REALLY long story, and I don't really want to type it all out. Most people know what happened anyway (Its just a story about cops being dicks.. if you want to hear it call me and I will fill you in.)

Now I am off to study at the library, and then run at the rec center... thats right, I am super productive!

So this week was hard. I had 2 tests and a 4 page paper due. On top of all of that I was fighting with all my room mates, and that was horrible. We were in an all out war, and nothing was really being accomplished but everyone was getting more and more pissed. We got into a screaming match and worked it all out.. so that is a lot of stress off my shoulders. I struggled all week on my work and then my TA's shit all over my hard work today. My TA in accounting said that very few people did well on the test tuesday, and my Russian Culture TA said that people didnt understand the paper assignment... 20 min before its due. YES! So I get out of my Russian lab, and see one of my good friends, who totally blows me off. I don't know why... maybe because of who he was with... but I was upset. Than I was going to cook dinner for the guys,... but most of them were busy so it was Me and Chris (Aaron and Adam came over too, so it wasn't wasted). But thats enough bitching!!!

So it is Friday night, and I am bound and determined to have a good weekend. Hopefully Katie and I will go to the mall tomorrow, and there is supposed to be a big party off Pimlico (Brad and Schotte's) so tomorrow should be good. So far tonight I am watching Boston and Chris play Mario Tennis... I hope it picks up soon.

Well if you have anything to do this weekend give me a call, I'm glad I ranted and got it out of my system.

So this weekend was AMAZING!!! Friday I went to dinner with two of my aunts, and then we went to the balloon glow in Forest Park. It was so magical... I felt like a 3 year old because I was mesmerized. 

Saturday I went to my Dad's house... he changed my oil, filled my car with gas, took me to lunch, and got me a mini fridge. I had to study Nutrition, which ended in a phenomenal nap (because nutrition is boring). Later that night I went to Nick Hall's house and hung out with the guys. It was fun, but not huge.. but its not about how big a party is, its how much fun the people you are surrounded with are.

Today I did the family thing.. which I enjoy. I have a really interesting family. My little cousin (who is 5) followed me around for most of the day. I think its cute, and I like kids so I felt special. I heard some stories about my Grandma that were interesting (she used to be quite the drinker) and just hung out all day. My brother got me the new Dane Cook CD, and that makes me very happy. I have heard amazing things... and I must admit so far it is good. Well, I made the drive back to columbia.. windows down... ROCKING out to random songs the whole way. 

Now I have to say... I have some great friends. When I got back, I had the mini fridge (which is actually quite large...) which I couldn't get up 3 flights of stairs if my life depended on it... so Boston and Chris came over to bring it to my room. I have some great friends... and that made my already amazing day that much better. 

Now I am very sleepy, so I am going to bed. Thank you very much everyone who wished me a happy birthday... I have some great friends!!

I had a HUGE math test today, and now it is finally over so I can stop stressing. I literally had nightmares for days about it. I feel as if I did well... so we will see. I am so excited about life right now, no math class tomorrow, I get to see my family, eat amazing food, and study.. but other than that last one it should be great.

I think Boston and Jim might call me to hang out sat night, so I might go out there (crossing the river... OH NO!) but I'm not really sure yet. Hopefully I can find some gas tomorrow... Break Time was all out and the lady was a bitch... that made it worse. Well, because I am boring and tired I am going to bed... I will write all about my birthday on sunday.. which will be interesting to me and nobody else will probably care.. but oh well. You'll read what I tell you to, and you will like it!!!

Thursday I have a math test, so all week is devoted to study time. I am exhausted at the moment from to much work and not nearly enough sleep. I wanted to write a quick update anyway. This weekend I am going home for my birthday (which is sunday for anyone who wants to know).

I have been stressing lately over my classes and boys, and everything is really falling into place. I seem to be understanding my math well, (or at least I am working through the problems without having to step back and cool off to figure out the answers...) And my other classes aren't as boring as they have been. (That is one thing that sucks about being a business major... boring class after boring class that all pour into each other.) I delt with the relationship issues, and I feel much better. I think I will continue to go running a few times a week, I HATE running but I feel amazing after I do, so I guess it works out in the end.

So I am on campus, I have a 2 hour break, my cell phone is almost dead (can't call anyone) and I don't have my ipod. Livejournal seemed like a good thing to occupy some time. 

I am SO excited that it is Friday. Today I have 3 classes, and 3 hours of breaks in between. Of course my last class isn't canceled, but it is my Russian class, and I like it most of the time. The professor is a little monotone (I mean, I laugh because I always think of steven hawking when I am in his class...) but today is my lab, and the TA is really cool. 

Next weekend I am going home for my birthday. As of Sunday the 18th I am no longer a teenager. I am excited to go home... going home every now and then is nice. I'm not going to lie, I am excited about my birthday. Who doesn't like their own birthday?

September 30th I might be going to KC to see Jason Mraz, but I don't know if it will happen or not. The tickets are 5 bucks through anyone who goes there, but you can only get one ticket per student ID. There are like... somewhere between 6 and 8 of us who want to go. So the 2 or 3 people who know people there would have to find 8 of their friends willing to go buy tickets for some random people, and who also didn't plan on going to see Jason Mraz for 5 bucks in the first place. I don't know anyone at UMKC, so I guess I am SOL. Also... everyone is staying with some girls I don't know, and you never really know if it is cool to bring another girl. Sometimes girls don't like other girls tagging along. I would like to go... so hopefully I will get a ticket... but its not the end of the world if I don't make it.

In October I am going camping with a bunch of the guys for Jim's birthday. I've never been camping before so I am really excited. I am also nervous because I know I'm not easy to get along with for long periods of time... I mean... I am just going to admit when I get hungry I get cranky, I hate bugs, and I am VERY sensitive to temperature. I have this all under control... bring a box of granola bars, it will be October so there shouldn't be many bugs, and lastly it wont be hot, so all I have to worry about is wearing layers. Plus how amazing are all the trees in Missouri going to look in mid October? (Hopefully really amazing.)

Sidebar- there is a guy across from me in the Hitt Street computer lab listening to... I shit you not... a WALKMAN! Like, old school 80's large sony headphones and all. This makes me smile. At one point I had a bright yellow walkman that was huge... and I loved it. (Ok, I stole it from my Dad, but it was sweet.) anyway... thats all...

I know this was like the most pointless random Live Journal ever... but I am bored. I still have an hour and 10 min before I have to get to class. AHHH

I am going to rant, and this might not even be coherent... I am just a little worked up and I need to vent. Read it if you want, and leave a message if you have an opinion.

Ok... Lately I have been a little high strung! I am kind of upset about my classes, and I am just worried. I've got some hard classes this semester and I think everything is going ok, but I am worried that its NOT. So I am trying to relax, and study, and calm my mind. Another part is relationship problems. Most of you know what I am talking about.. so I'm not really going into any background... here goes..

I know people always talk about how they can change.. but can they? I mean, droping bad habits is one thing, but where is the line between a bad habit and the simple fact that just is your personality? I don't know if people can change who they are. We might like to think that we can, but haven't you found that you always fall into your habits? I crack my knuckles, and I don't even realize I do it 90 percent of the time, it just happens. So maybe its always like that, maybe people yell, and they don't realize how bad it is, or they say hurtful things and don't even think twice about how that effect other people. 

So what is a bad habit that someone can stop if they really put their mind to it, and what is just human nature that will always creep back into their daily lives? And at what point is it just to late to salvage anything? Maybe you really CAN change, but maybe whoever you want to change for has already taken way to much shit and is just fed up, and can't forget everything.

I am always on guard, waiting for a relapse, waiting for that call or text message, where I am in the same situation, and I feel trapped... good intentions or not. I don't know... when is it just to much?


Please respond... if you have any opinion whatsoever.

So Sunday I went to the guys apartment in the afternoon and we hung out until I had to go to church. A pizza arrived just as I was getting back, which was amazing because I was hungry. Jim had already been pregaming all afternoon, so I knew the night was off to a good start. A few of their friends came in from St. Louis, and of course the 4 that live there, Adam, Aaron, me, Charlotte, and Jessie all kicked off the party. Over all it was amazing, but there were a few parts that were weird... There was unpleasant words had between one of the guys and an old friend of theirs... which resulted in the girls leaving... then later some guys showed up that were just not being cool for some reason. Jim apparently was "burning bridges". Later in the night Chris busted out Jim's pimp shirt... and then we all got our hands on anything we could (Jim also had a bunch of dew rags, and ryan has a pimp shirt also) It was SO funny! If anyone wants to see go to my webshots.. there are a million pictures of the whole night. Anyway, I went to cook breakfast in the morning but nobody was up until like 12, so I slept on some little cot thing on the floor until everyone woke up. 

Charlotte came over the next day and Boston Jim and I went to help her with an interview thing, she had to ask somebody questions (being videotaped) and it can't be a student. We found this really funny guy... his occupation: Rock and Roller. (keep in mind this guy had all white hair, I mean he could have been 60 easily) In the middle his friend came up and started talking to us, and was talking about how it wasn't to late for Boston to find God (the lecture was brought about when the guy looked at his shirt which had a pot leaf on it..) This guy even said where there's one it goes right down the line and tried to accuse me of smoking... I was like hey man.. I am clean! The guys were very amusing, and it was just one of those things that makes you think.. how many crazy people are there who's main income is some band when they are in their 50's, and who thats all they do is walk around downtown columbia in their dew rags talking about how Jesus saves lives... They should meet brother Jed. ha ha...

Anyway I had a great weekend... and now I am back to school work (working ahead in math because I am DEDICATED!!)

Friday Travis came to see me, and when I got to his car I saw a huge bouquet of Orange Lillies (I love lillies). We hung out for a while and went to Ross street to hang out with the guys, and to my surprise they all got along really well. I didn't know how they would really take each other... but everyone got along great and we all had a blast (well, I did, and I think everyone else did too) Drunk Jim is like one of the funniest things ever. He says some great stuff... but then again drunk kids always amuse me.

Yesterday we went to LSD (lee street deli) with Jim, Boston, Ryan, and Jim's parents. Jim's parents were pretty cool... anyway... Later that day I continued my bad luck streak... I haven't written about it yet so I will sum it up really quick

1) It rained really hard last friday, and on my way to campus I got splashed by 3 cars on the side of the road, and by the time i got to Cornell my pants were soaked up to the back pockets (literally). So I go to the bathroom and ring out my pants, but 2 girls walked in and saw half my ass while I was doing it. (It could have been worse... lets just say it wasn't a thong, but it wasn't granny panties.) By the end of the day I laughed it off.. it was pretty funny

2) A few days later my math teacher singled me out and embarrassed me in front of our whole class... long story short I started to cry, and had to do a make up assignment. As I am still all red in the face and sniffling I realize I don't have my book because I didn't think I would need it for the day, so then like 10 people around me who feel bad for me because I am making an ass out of myself crying start looking for books for me to borrow... All ended well... nobody laughed at me to my face, and I didn't get a zero...

3) Later that day I cut my finger with a butter knife

4) I was baking cookies and SOMEONE (cough-Boston-cough) turned off the oven, and the cookies looked like huge pancakes... they covered the baking sheet from side to side. The guys all laughed at me for them turning out bad... but then we figured out what the problem had been and the next batch was a little better. (Basically, I made unsuccessful cookies, and that is one thing I KNOW I am good at is baking...)

5) I bit my lip eating a grape and I keep biting the same spot because its huge... and it hurts

6) On top of all those things I was fighting with travis A LOT

7) Now for the kicker... the one that happened yesterday... I go to cook some dinner (Travis is taking out the trash for me) and as soon as the burner heats up on my stove it lights on fire. I mean a HUGE monster flames a foot and a half tall. I freak out, and it wont go out, I put a lid on it, and it was smoking like a bitch, then the smoke detector starts going nuts, I am all alone looking for baking soda shaking thinking my apartment is going to burn down, I cant ever find any baking soda, and eventually the fire smothers itself out... but the smoke detector is still going nuts. I open all the windows and wave smoke away from the detector and get it all under control, but everyone in my building was coming out trying to figure out whos alarm was going off and... it sucked. bad.

Anyway, later last night we went to Don Newman's and I saw some old friends. I got a random text message from someone that pissed me off from that same group of old friends... I don't know if it was related because the kid who sent it wasn't in town. Travis left this morning, and today is Boston's birthday so I will be going to hang out with the boys shortly, and I will probably be there all day... I hope I have some crazy stories to write and some crazy pictures to put up after tonight...
